The paper discusses a machine learning technique called conformal prediction, which can be applied to various methods such as nearest-neighbor, support-vector machines, and regression. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of Gaussian linear models, which falls under the sub-category of statistics (cs.ST), and the application of conformal prediction in an on-line setting, which could be relevant to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
